2 types of elements
1. static elements  --> Name , Id
2. Dynamic elements -->

1. The elements after every refresh changes the value
2. The elements will not show name / id

Xpaths --> xtended paths -- path that a user travels through html code

1. Relative Xpaths --> travel based on syntax --> >90%
//*[@id="tblcrtac"]/tbody/tr[3]/td[3]/input
//*[@id="tblcrtac"]/tbody/tr[9]/td[3]/input
//*[@id="tblcrtac"]/tbody/tr[32]/td[3]/input
2. Absolute xpaths --> travel based on tagnames --> >80%
/html/body/center/form/div/table[2]/tbody/tr[3]/td[3]/input

/html/body/center/form/div/table[2]/tbody/tr[3]/td[3]/input


Frameworks - structural ways to represent  a code
1. keyword driven --> control with keywords
2. Data driven --> control with data 
3. Hybrid [keyword + data]

1. Test NG -- Java dependent    - Keyword Driven --> Hybrids
2. Cucumber -- Any programming language - Keyword Driven --> Hybrids


Annotations --> Controls the execution in testng

1. @Test  - write test cases
2. @BeforeTest - Preconditions
3. @AfterTest - Postconditions
###################################
4. @BeforeClass -- Utilities before start of class
5. @AfterClass  -- Utilities after end of class
_________________________________________
6. @BeforeMethod -- Runs before the method
7. @AfterMethod  -- Runs after the method
--------------------------------------
8. @BeforeSuite -- Runs before the test suite
9. @AfterSuite --  Runs after the test suite
---------------------------------------
 
 Concept of assertions
 
 1. Soft assertion  -- 
 2. Hard assertion  -- something needs to be passed mandatorily
 
